<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='621000' id='t-621000'>And so, I kept my eyes peeled</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='623000' id='t-623000'>to see if the sort of changes that happened</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='625000' id='t-625000'>when we went from pre-print comics to print comics</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='628000' id='t-628000'>would happen when we went beyond, to post-print comics.</span>
</span>
</p>
<p class='talk-transcript__para'>
<data class='talk-transcript__para__time'>
10:42
</data>
<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='631000' id='t-631000'>So, one of the first things that were proposed</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='633000' id='t-633000'>was that we could mix the visuals of comics</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='635000' id='t-635000'>with the sound, motion and interactivity</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='637000' id='t-637000'>of the CD-ROMs that were being made in those days.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='639000' id='t-639000'>This was even before the Web.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='641000' id='t-641000'>And one of the first things they did was,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='642000' id='t-642000'>they tried to take the comics page as-is</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='644000' id='t-644000'>and transplant it to monitors,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='645000' id='t-645000'>which was a classic McLuhanesque mistake</span>
