</p>
<p class='talk-transcript__para'>
<data class='talk-transcript__para__time'>
12:36
</data>
<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='745000' id='t-745000'>And I thought, O.K., well,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='746000' id='t-746000'>if that's true, is there any way,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='749000' id='t-749000'>when we go beyond today's print,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='751000' id='t-751000'>to somehow bring that back?</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='754000' id='t-754000'>Now, the monitor</span>
